There's no way...

408
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,040
What hard work?

409
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:44,720
Signed and sealed. The sale documents.

410
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:45,760
Everything is here.

411
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,800
Take a closer look.

412
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:55,260
[Register of Pawns]

413
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:56,260
[Green jade hairpin]

414
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,840
Take a good look. Is it his handwriting?

415
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:01,960
Done?

416
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:03,600
We're leaving.

417
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:06,100
[Gold ring, gold bracelet]

418
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:15,920
Magistrate, this way.

419
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:30,640
Magistrate, have you ever
deeply loved a woman?

420
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:33,240
There used to be a scholar

421
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,520
who loved a woman so much.

422
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,920
But this woman was trapped
in the world of prostitution.

423
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:37,840
So

424
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:40,080
he needed money to buy her out.

425
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:43,680
Mr. Zhong believed
in this love story

426
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:45,200
and accepted his heirloom.

427
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:46,720
Can you guess

428
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:48,680
how much is this pawn worth?

429
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:52,240
Such a gold ring

430
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,280
is worth...

431
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:56,600
[5,000 wen]
5,000 wen?

432
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:58,280
Moreover,

433
00:22:58,720 --> 00:23:00,360
Magistrate, you're mistaken.

434
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:01,600
This ring

435
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:03,040
is not gold at all.

436
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:04,840
Like this,

437
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:05,880
Mr. Zhong

438
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,760
was always moved

439
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:08,320
by these scammers' love stories.

440
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:09,640
So,

441
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,280
there are quite a few pawns here

442
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:12,920
that have no value.

443
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,920
I also found

444
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:19,040
that valuable items are missing.

445
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,400
Actually, I have been thinking

446
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:23,160
our shopkeeper

447
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,680
must be aware of this.

448
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,800
Haven't you tried to persuade him?

449
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,560
I did.

450
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:30,160
But

451
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:31,400
after

452
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,440
a few useless persuasions,

453
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:34,960
would you still do it again?

454
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:28,680
I also found...

455
00:24:28,780 --> 00:24:29,380
[Register of Pawns]

456
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,200
[Gold ring, gold bracelet]
that valuable items are missing.

457
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,420
[Gold bracelet]

458
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,960
Miss Cao, have you heard

459
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,280
about the woman in the watchtower?

460
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:22,640
Magistrate has come

461
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:23,960
to inquire.

462
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:28,920
In answer to your question, Magistrate,

463
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:30,600
I have seen her.

464
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,560
You have?

465
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:34,760
Where?

466
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:36,400
In the theater.

467
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:37,920
She was watching a shadow play.

468
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:39,480
Then what?

469
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:43,160
One day when I went out,

470
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,360
I happened to see the puppet troupe

471
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,040
performing "Rain Master" in the theater.

472
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:50,160
That lady was also among the crowd.

473
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:52,840
That day,

474
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,920
the expression on her face

475
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,720
suggested she was very engrossed.

476
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,520
Just like a child,

477
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:00,440
crying and laughing.

478
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,160
After the performance,

479
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,480
she kept asking the members of the troupe

480
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:08,240
how Rain Master could come back to life.

481
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:11,400
It seemed that she couldn't distinguish
between the play and reality.

482
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,520
As if in this world,

483
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:16,120
there truly was a Rain Master.

484
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,720
When was that?

485
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,280
Six months ago.

486
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:26,320
Thank you for providing
such valuable information.

487
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,560
That's not necessary.

488
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,320
Magistrate.

489
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,160
Do you have anything else?

490
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,200
What else can I have?

491
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,680
These days,

492
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,560
I have been occupied
by this watchtower case.

493
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:47,640
I haven't listened to your music for long.

494
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:48,760
I remember

495
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:51,440
the other day you mentioned
"Song of Xunyang" to me.

496
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,320
About what Magistrate inquired,

497
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,320
I have already told you everything I know.

498
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,280
If there is nothing else to ask,

499
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,120
please excuse me, I've got to rest.

500
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,560
Where have you been in the midnight?

501
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,080
You were waiting for me?

502
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,840
I have some good news to tell you.

503
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:51,080
What good news?

504
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,360
Last night,

505
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,080
I told Cao An
about the upcoming transfer

506
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,160
of the Magistrate.

507
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,400
How can you be so silly?

508
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,160
What's wrong with me doing that?

509
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:01,120
Magistrate is about to leave,
no doubt about it.

510
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:03,000
I'm doing this for her own good.

511
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:04,240
To help her cut off all attachments.

512
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:07,520
Where did it come from?

513
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:09,160
You stole something again!

514
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:09,920
Shh!

515
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:11,880
Come on! This is not stealing.

516
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,680
We're leaving.

517
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:14,920
I did it just for the keepsake.

518
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,800
After all we've been through,

519
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,960
you still can't kick
the habit of stealing.

520
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:41,520
A leopard can't change its spots, indeed.

521
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:46,560
Magistrate!

522
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,000
Magistrate.

523
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,200
Magistrate, I'll give her
a piece of my mind.

524
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,360
Don't be angry, Magistrate.

525
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:02,320
Come in quickly.

526
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:02,960
Take shelter from the rain,

527
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:03,840
you fool!

528
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,440
Are you stupid?

529
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:11,880
Leave me alone!

530
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,040
Just swallow your pride a little.
It won't hurt you!

531
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:32,880
You see,

532
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:34,760
it seems to have grown.

533
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:36,720
But it will take a few more years

534
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,480
before it blooms and bears fruit.

535
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:41,360
All in good time.

536
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:45,520
Miss Cao.

537
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:48,800
The straw rain cape is very good.

538
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:50,920
I like it very much.

539
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:52,280
Glad you like it.

540
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:09,520
Six months ago, Mr. Zhong

541
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:11,800
watched a shadow play
by a puppet troupe in the city.

542
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:13,520
After he came back,

543
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,080
he was too preoccupied
to feel an appetite...

544
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:16,720
Like this,

545
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:17,920
Mr. Zhong

546
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,640
was always moved

547
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,320
by these scammers' love stories.

548
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,120
After the performance,

549
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:25,480
she kept asking the members of the troupe

550
00:30:26,520 --> 00:30:28,160
how Rain Master could come back to life.

551
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:31,480
Seemed that she couldn't
distinguish between the play and reality.

552
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,560
As if in this world,

553
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:36,240
there truly was a Rain Master.

554
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,200
Magistrate.

555
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,120
It's raining.

556
00:30:58,600 --> 00:30:59,400
Magistrate.

557
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:02,120
It's raining heavily.

558
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,080
She's still out there in the rain.

559
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:26,320
She knows she was wrong.

560
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:45,600
Come in.

561
00:32:14,620 --> 00:32:18,220
[Xiang's Fabric Shop]

562
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:44,480
Looks a bit like Rain Master.

563
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:57,480
I got it!

564
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,520
Whoever puts on Rain Master's clothes

565
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:00,800
becomes Rain Master!

566
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:49,920
Why haven't you come for so many days?

567
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:52,080
Do you know I've been waiting
for you every day?

568
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:55,600
Do you know how much I miss you?

569
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,200
How come you're so quiet?

570
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:02,320
What's wrong?

571
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,040
Why aren't you speaking?

